cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.DS 

This paper discusses the use of data analytics in networking, specifically in the context of Software Defined Networking (SDN). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the architecture and programming model for real-time and one-pass networking data analytics, which involves joint in-network and out-of-network computing, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the security implications of the proposed system, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper proposes a general MapReduce-like programming model, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
